Description: Eastwood Guitars Devo Whip It Guitar Solid body Electric Guitar - Inspired by Bob1’s Original Whip It guitar DEVO had some strange instruments over the years - like the La Baye 2x4 and the Be Stiff Bass that Eastwood Reissued previously. To carry the tradition further, they added Bob1's "Whip It" guitar to the Devo Signature Model Lineup! This Eastwood guitar is modelled after the original guitar that was customized by Bob1 during the time DEVO was working on their “Freedom of Choice” album in 1979/1980. While Bob was not a professional guitar customizer, it is interesting to note that these unique instruments were ‘Frankensteined’ by guys who were - like their music - just inspired to do something different than the norm. Bob1's original "Whip It" guitar was basically a solid body guitar modified with the lower horn cut off and flipped over. It is a 24 3/4" scale guitar, mahogany body with maple top, set maple neck, dual humbuckers, dual volume and tone controls with a stop tail and a dark cherry finish. I have had this guitar in my personal collection for a year, but haven't given it the attention it deserves.  It's time for me to cut down my collection so this one is for sale.   Features: • Mahogany Body with Maple Cap • Set Neck with Bound Fingerboard • 24 ¾” scale • Medium “C” shaped profile • Dual Humbucking Pickups • Dual Volume Controls • Dual Tone Controls • Gold Hardware • Nashville Tune-o-Matic style bridge • Stop Tailpiece • Case: Gig Bag Included!
Title: Eastwood "Whip It" Guitar - Devo Signature Solid Body
